      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JAZZY BOO (1) was checked in the run and safely held when fourth (20.29) in a Grade 6 over 342m at Angle Park. Good beginner and aided by the inside draw. Has the ability and looks hard to top. FERNANDO LEE (2) flew the lids from the middle with an impressive turn of foot, going on to clock 17.68 when a half a length winner over 305m at this track. Solid formlines coming through his last run. Leading chance again. CADILLAC RAGTOP (8) turned in a moderate run last time when sixth at this track over 305m behind Cadillac Belle (18.26) in a Grade 4. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Should be about the money. BULSARA (6) missed the placings here most recently but can sneak into the finish with the right run.",
